Happy #NationalTwinDay to our favorite twinners!

I will take any opportunity to celebrate these two and the special little miracles they are, even if it is on one of these random made up days! 😉

Fun fact: When I was little I was always annoyed that my mom hadn’t given me a twin. I was obsessed with Mary-Kate and Ashley and didn’t understand why my mom wasn’t thoughtful enough to give me a best friend.
Turns out, God has a sense of humor and even though I never got my own twin, I got the next best thing ❤️

Not many people are lucky enough to go through life with their bestie, let alone share the exact same DNA, but I am so glad I get to witness the amazing bond these two have and will carry through life.
#twinningiswinning #twinmom #identicaltwins #twingirls #twinsisters 👯‍♀️

I don’t have a crafty bone in my body and have never tried a TikTok trend before, but these #potterybarn terracotta pumpkin dupes got me! 
I was literally on my way to throw out all my old orange plastic pumpkins and buy all new cute ones this year, but a quick Home Depot trip and $18 later - voilà! They turned out so much better than I expected and were SO easy!

• I used the color Pottery Wheel by @behrpaint
• I used less baking soda mixed in than some recommend because I didn’t like it as textured, but it’s all preference! Just add more baking soda for a more textured look!

It’s our favorite guys birthday today and there’s no one who deserves to be celebrated more than @kstew6!!
You have four girls that think the absolute world of you ❤️
Happy birthday @kstew6! 🎉

Just a few snaps from this past week 📷

It’s been quite the week at the Stewart house!
@kstew6 tearing his Achilles on his birthday and surgery a few days later wasn’t quite the birthday present he expected, but he’s had a few pretty cute nurses taking good care of him this week at his beck and call. 
We also had Harper’s annual cardiac appointment at Primary Children’s and got some really good news. There were some concerns with her echo last year that she may have LVNC (Left Ventricular Non-Compaction Cardiomyopathy) but this year her echo showed less trabeculation in the ventricle and enough improvement that she will be seen every other year now ❤️
This may not make a lot of sense to anyone else, but for us, it’s a huge win. From having zero function of the left side of her heart to where she’s at now is nothing short of amazing and we were so grateful to get this positive update!
With our week of health ups and downs, it truly makes you realize what the most important things are in life 🫶🏼

“She’s a middle mom. There’s no longer baby on her hip, but she’s not yet misty eyed, marveling over caps and gowns. If you look far enough into the back of her kitchen cupboard, you just might still find a sippy cup.
There’s a chance there’s a few bath toys in a long, unused bin, because before she realized it happened showers became the usual. She’s far enough into motherhood to know just how fast it all goes, but not yet fully through the land of little. She’s in a space that lingers between babies and bigs.
And she’s soaking it in. She’ll read “the one more book” whenever she can. She’ll hold the snuggles a little longer and a little closer. She savors, as she can feel the rush of time.
She grabs all of today because she’s a middle mom.” 
• Emily Roussell

I had one of those weird realizations today that my girls are growing up. You know, one of those gut-punch-holy-cow-how-did-we-get-here realizations that hit you hard because everyone was right and it really does happen WAY too fast.

I’m kind of loving this middle mom phase, but also can’t really believe we actually made it here some days. 

Are you a middle mom? How many babies do you have and what are their ages? ❤️
